Danio rerio", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9449767470359802, "span": {"begin": 1041, "end": 1052}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:4513"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "COX-2", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9900833368301392, "span": {"begin": 1069, "end": 1074}}, {"id": ["mesh:C000228"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "aristolochic acid", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9993077516555786, "span": {"begin": 1085, "end": 1102}}, {"id": ["CHEBI:64816"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "doxorubicin", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9995015859603882, "span": {"begin": 1107, "end": 1118}}, {"id": ["mesh:D006332"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "hypertrophy of the heart", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9999897480010986, "span": {"begin": 1128, "end": 1152}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "cardiomyocytes", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.7236037254333496, "span": {"begin": 1173, "end": 1187}}, {"id": ["mesh:D004696"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "loss of endocardium", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9998867511749268, "span": {"begin": 1193, "end": 1212}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:7955"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "zebrafish", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9516890645027161, "span": {"begin": 1327, "end": 1336}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:1351"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "COX", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.8374778032302856, "span": {"begin": 1358, "end": 1361}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:9606"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "humans", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9863823652267456, "span": {"begin": 1443, "end": 1449}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:9031"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "chicken", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9672616720199585, "span": {"begin": 1451, "end": 1458}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:9031"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Gallus gallus", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9499931931495667, "span": {"begin": 1460, "end": 1473}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:8090"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Japanese medaka", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9510940909385681, "span": {"begin": 1480, "end": 1495}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:8090"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Oryzias latipes", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9707338213920593, "span": {"begin": 1497, "end": 1512}}], "text": "Blocking induction of COX-2 through knockdown of COX-2 or through selective antagonists of COX-2 &nbsp;in zebrafish, Japanese medaka (Oryzias latipes), and chicken (Gallus gallus)&nbsp;prevents alteration in cardiovascular development and function by 2,3,7,8-TCDD, including prevention of pericardial edema, changes in heart size, and reduction in blood blow (Dong et al 2010; Teraoka et al 2008; 2014).  Knockdown of and selective antagonists of thromboxane A synthase 1 (CYP5A), which is down-stream of COX-2 in the prostaglandin synthesis pathway, prevents alteration in cardiovascular development and function by 2,3,7,8-TCDD&nbsp;(Teraoka et al 2008).   COX-2 Cardiovascular Development Roles:    Transgenic mice (Mus musculus) that over express COX-2 display altered cardiac remodeling&nbsp;that results in cardiomyocyte hypertrophy&nbsp;(Streicher et al 2010). However, significantly impaired cardiac function was not observed in the strain of transgenic mice investigated in this study (Streicher et al 2010).  Embryos of zebrafish (Danio rerio) exposed to the COX-2 inducers, aristolochic acid and doxorubicin, develop hypertrophy of the heart, disorganization of cardiomyocytes, and loss of endocardium (Huang et al 2007). These&nbsp;effects result&nbsp;in reduced function of the heart and eventually cause death in zebrafish (Huang et al 2007).  COX-2 has also been demonstrated&nbsp;to have roles in cardiovascular development in humans, chicken (Gallus gallus), and Japanese medaka (Oryzias latipes) (Fujisawa et al 2014; Gullestad &amp; Aukrust 2005; Hocherl et al 2002; Huang et al 2007; Wong et al 1998).&nbsp;", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 14:33:46 +0000 2026"}